Core.Line: Hey, what are you doing there?
None of your business.
You don't want this! You can do better than this, right?
Don't you dare.
The violent persion leaves without a word.
Are you okay?
I'm fine. It does not hurt as much as it appears.
Are you defending him?
He has a tough history.
Okay, wow! You do your thing. I'm in a hurry.
Where are you going?
Mount Uphill. I have something to ... (Sigh) Forget it.
I know that place. I can take you there.
Really? But what do you get from this?
Quality time I guess? By the way, I'm Bookworm.
... Island. I think it's my name.
Island agrees that they will go together, and tells Bookworm his story in Nowhere.
That is... pretty messed up, huh?
I'm not anxious. I just feel sad, about my amnesia.
It's alright. Having feelings is a great step to having memories back, isn't it?
I sure hope so.
